<div class="body" id="fhbody-175361335">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-175361335" class="p">
			
		 	
				Apple has boosted the default RAM to 16GB across its MacBook Air lineup while maintaining existing prices. The memory upgrade <a href="https://www.engadget.com/computing/laptops/every-macbook-air-now-starts-with-16gb-of-ram-at-no-extra-cost-150041320.html">affects both M2 and M3 models</a>, with base prices staying at $999 for M2, $1,099 for 13-inch M3, and $1,299 for 15-inch M3 versions. The move comes as AI features demand increased memory capacity.
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
